}{\plain \fs26 \fs26 To amend Chapter 5 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to ethics \softline
in government, so as to change certain provisions relating to powers and duties of the \softline
Georgia Government Transparency and Campaign Finance Commission; to revise definitions \softline
relating to ethics in government; to change certain provisions relating to campaign \softline
contribution disclosure reports; to change certain provisions relating to filing campaign \softline
contribution disclosure reports; to change certain provisions relating to acceptance of \softline
contributions or pledges during legislative sessions; to change certain provisions relating to \softline
financial disclosure statement filings by public officers, filings by candidates for public \softline
office, filing by elected officials and members of the General Assembly, electronic filing, and \softline
transfer of filings from the Secretary of State to the Georgia Government Transparency and \softline
Campaign Finance Commission; to provide an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and \softline
for other purposes.\par
