{\plain \fs26 \fs26 \par
}\pard \fs26\qc\sl360\slmult1\keepn\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 }{\plain \fs26 \b\fs26 SECTION 3.}{\plain \fs26 \fs26 \par
}\pard \fs26\qj\sl360\slmult1\keepn\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 21-5-34, relating to campaign \softline
contribution disclosure reports, as follows:\par
}\pard \fs26\qj\li187\sl360\slmult1\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 {\u698\'20}21-5-34.\par
}\pard \fs26\qj\li547\sl360\slmult1\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 (a)(1)(A)  The candidate or the chairperson or treasurer of each campaign committee \softline
organized to bring about the nomination or election of a candidate for any office and \softline
the chairperson or treasurer of every campaign committee designed to bring about the \softline
recall of a public officer or to oppose the recall of a public officer or designed to bring \softline
about the approval or rejection by the voters of any proposed constitutional amendment, \softline
state-wide proposed question, or state-wide referendum shall electronically sign and file \softline
with the commission the required campaign contribution disclosure reports}{\plain \fs26 \ul\fs26 ; provided, \softline
however, that public offices listed in subparagraph (F) or (G) of paragraph (22) of Code \softline
Section 21-5-3 shall be subject to signing and filing requirements as prescribed by \softline
paragraph (3) or (4) of this subsection, and recalls for such offices shall be subject to 
signing and filing requirements the same as required of candidates for such offices as \softline
prescribed by paragraph (3) or (4) of this subsection}{\plain \fs26 \fs26 .\par
}\pard \fs26\qj\li547\sl360\slmult1\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 (B)  The chairperson or treasurer of each independent committee shall file the required \softline
disclosure reports with the commission.\par
}\pard \fs26\qj\li547\sl360\slmult1\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 (2)(A)  Any campaign committee which accepts contributions or makes expenditures \softline
designed to bring about the approval or rejection by the voters of any proposed question \softline
which is to appear on the ballot in this state }{\plain \fs26 \strike\fs26 or in a county or a municipal election in this \softline
state}{\plain \fs26 \fs26  shall register with the commission and file campaign contribution disclosure \softline
reports as prescribed by this chapter }{\plain \fs26 \ul\fs26 or, in the case of any proposed question which is \softline
to appear on the ballot in a county or municipal election, shall register and file \softline
campaign disclosure reports with the same officials as prescribed by paragraph (3) \softline
or\~(4) of this subsection for candidates for county or municipal offices}{\plain \fs26 \fs26 ; provided, \softline
however, that such reports shall only be required if such campaign committee has \softline
received contributions which total more than $500.00 or if such campaign committee \softline
has made expenditures which total more than $500.00.  All advertising pertaining to \softline
referendums shall identify the principal officer of such campaign committee by listing \softline
or stating the name and title of the principal officer.\par
}\pard \fs26\qj\li547\sl360\slmult1\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 (B)  If a campaign committee is required to file a report }{\plain \fs26 \ul\fs26 with the commission}{\plain \fs26 \fs26  under \softline
subparagraph (A) of this paragraph, such report shall be electronically filed }{\plain \fs26 \strike\fs26 with the \softline
commission}{\plain \fs26 \fs26 .  Any such report shall be filed 15 days prior to the date of the election; \softline
and a final report shall be filed prior to December 31 of the election year.\par
}\pard \fs26\qj\li360\sl360\slmult1\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \fs26 }{\plain \fs26 \ul\fs26 (3)  A candidate for a public office listed in subparagraph (F) of paragraph (22) of Code \softline
Section 21-5-3 or the chairperson or treasurer of such candidate's campaign committee \softline
shall sign and file the required disclosure reports with the election superintendent in the \softline
county of election.  Upon receipt of any such report, the election superintendent shall \softline
cause such report to be available for inspection and copying in accordance with Article \softline
4 of Chapter 18 of Title 50.  The election superintendent shall transmit a copy of each \softline
such report to the commission, electronically by eFiling or eFax, not later than 30 days \softline
after the end of the grace period.  No fine, fee, or sanction, including but not limited to \softline
identifying a candidate as having filed late or failed to file, shall be imposed by the \softline
commission on a candidate for the failure of the election superintendent to timely \softline
transmit a copy of such report.\par
}\pard \fs26\qj\li360\sl360\slmult1\tx187\tx360\tx547\tx720\tx907\tx1080\tx1267\tx1440\tx1627\tx2160\tx1987\tx2160\tx2347\tx-1436\tx2707\tx2880\tx3067\tx-1436\tx3427\tx-1435\tx3787\tx-1435\tx4147\tx4320\tx4507\tx-1435\tx4867\tx5040\tx5227 
{\plain \fs26 \ul\fs26 (4)  A candidate for a public office listed in subparagraph (G) of paragraph (22) of Code \softline
Section 21-5-3 or the chairperson or treasurer of such candidate's campaign committee \softline
shall sign and file the required disclosure reports with the municipal clerk in the \softline
municipality of election or, if there is no clerk, with the chief executive officer of the \softline
municipality; provided, however, that a municipality and a county may enter into an 
agreement whereby such candidates, chairpersons, or treasurers shall file the required \softline
disclosure reports with the county election superintendent instead.  Upon receipt of any \softline
such report, the municipal clerk, chief executive officer of the municipality, or county \softline
election superintendent, as applicable, shall cause such report to be available for \softline
inspection and copying in accordance with Article 4 of Chapter 18 of Title 50.  The \softline
municipal clerk, chief executive officer of the municipality, or county election \softline
superintendent, as applicable, shall transmit a copy of each such report to the \softline
commission, electronically by eFiling or eFax, not later than 30 days after the end of the \softline
grace period.  No fine, fee, or sanction, including but not limited to identifying a \softline
candidate as having filed late or failed to file, shall be imposed by the commission on a \softline
